   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Covid19:Relief for Vulnerable Communities in India</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Covid-19 has disproportionately affected marginalized communities in India with the loss of livelihoods, lack of food, poor awareness and access to health facilities as well as other basic needs. Educate Girls has identified 1,517  villages in rural India that are in dire need of support through a data-backed approach and is working with the local administration to support the relief efforts to distribute ration kits to underprivileged families through its network of 14,000 community volunteers.</narrative>
  </description>
